03/01/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police arrested on Saturday (January 2nd) banker Josip Protega, the former director of state-controlled Postanska Banka, in relation to a case involving the approval of high-risk credits. 
Protega, who headed the bank between late 2004 and August 2009, is one of a group of seven suspects. 
The remaining six were arrested last Wednesday. 
Protega was detained at the Croatian-Slovenian border after police issued an international arrest warrant for him. 
(Javno, Dnevnik, Vecernji List, AFP - 02/01/10)
